From 7427a53ad4331d30f8faae57b140c46808dd9350 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mason Chang <mason-cw.chang@mediatek.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Oct 2025 20:25:24 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: mtk_eth_soc: add RSS support

Implement Receive Side Scaling (RSS) hardware offload support. This
adds RSS configuration, hash key programming, and multi-queue
distribution to improve receive performance by distributing packets
across multiple CPU cores.

Signed-off-by: Mason Chang <mason-cw.chang@mediatek.com>
[dpawlik: ported from mtk-openwrt-feeds 25.12 kernel 6.12 to 6.18;
 adapted for 6.18 IRQ rework (mtk_get_irqs(), named IRQs, MTK_FE_IRQ_*
 constants); reconciled with existing patches 702 (threaded NAPI),
 949 (poll weight 256), 950 (register definitions)]
Signed-off-by: Daniel Pawlik <pawlik.dan@gmail.com>
